title: Independent candidate Tariq Saeed wins PK-107
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent Candidate Tariq Saeed won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-107, Lakki Marwat-III by securing 34,400 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat-e-Ullema Islam Pakistan (JUI) candidate Muhammad Fawad Raza who bagged 21,679 votes.
Votersâ€™ turn-out remained at 46.61 per cent.
